    <Project>https://github.com/jesposito/walkabout</Project>
    <Overview>
        Walkabout is a self-hosted flight deal monitoring system that tracks prices from Google Flights and alerts you to exceptional deals. &#xD;
        &#xD;
        Features: &#xD;
        - Monitor routes from your home airports &#xD;
        - Statistical deal detection (z-score analysis) &#xD;
        - Push notifications via ntfy or Discord &#xD;
        - Trip planning with date flexibility &#xD;
        - Server-rendered dashboard (no JavaScript required) &#xD;
        &#xD;
        Requires a PostgreSQL database (use the official postgres:15 container). &#xD;
        &#xD;
        API keys and notification settings are configured in-app via the Settings page. &#xD;
        &#xD;
        Created by Jed Esposito. Also check out Facet - a self-hosted personal profile platform: https://github.com/jesposito/Facet
    </Overview>
    <Beta>False</Beta>
    <Category>Productivity: Tools: Other: Status:Stable</Category>
    <ExtraSearchTerms>flight deals travel airfare price monitor google flights cheap flights airline deals trip planner notifications ntfy discord</ExtraSearchTerms>
    <Icon>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jesposito/unraid_templates/main/images/walkabout-icon.png</Icon>
